Streams
-------
 1. To store the group of elements as single entity Collection is used.
 2. Streams is used to process the data in the collection.
 3. The Streams is introduced in Java8 inside the java.util.*; package.
 
 Stream uses 2 mechanisms to the process the data in the collection are below,
 1. Filter - Based up on the condition filter can be used to filter the data in collection.
 2. Map - Whatever data we have in Source is updated/modified and stored in Target collection.
 		  It is an intermediate operation and used to transform the object from source to target collection.

Lambda expression are important to work with the Stream.
 
 FlatMap
 -------
 1. FlapMap is part of Map mechanism which can be used to process the complex data in collection.
 2. FlatMap basically returns the stream of objects.
 
